ra/rest/api/2/issue/12423791/comment/12726704","id":"12726704","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jmhodges","name":"jmhodges","emailAddress":"jeff at somethingsimilar dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jeff Hodges","active":true},"body":"I like the sound of this deep svn voodoo.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jmhodges","name":"jmhodges","emailAddress":"jeff at somethingsimilar dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jeff Hodges","active":true},"created":"2009-07-02T21:59:28.488+0000","updated":"2009-07-02T21:59:28.488+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12423791/comment/12726723","id":"12726723","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sandeep_tata","name":"sandeep_tata","emailAddress":"sandeep dot tata at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Sandeep Tata","active":true},"body":"The mixed line-endings drove me nuts when developing on Windows. Cygwin made everything worse. None of the eol settings in git would do the right thing. Standardizing on one set of endings would be cause for great joy!","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sandeep_tata","name":"sandeep_tata","emailAddress":"sandeep dot tata at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Sandeep Tata","active":true},"created":"2009-07-02T22:52:04.589+0000","updated":"2009-07-02T22:52:04.589+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12423791/comment/12726773","id":"12726773","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jbellis","name":"jbellis","emailAddress":"jbellis at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380"},"displayName":"Jonathan Ellis","active":true},"body":"I had no idea that existed.  Will it deal with the few files that have mixed line endings?","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jbellis","name":"jbellis","emailAddress":"jbellis at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=jbellis&avatarId=18380"},"displayName":"Jonathan Ellis","active":true},"created":"2009-07-03T02:32:43.841+0000","updated":"2009-07-03T02:32:43.841+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12423791/comment/12726781","id":"12726781","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=euphoria","name":"euphoria","emailAddress":"michael dot greene at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Michael Greene","active":true},"body":"I don't think it would handle them properly, although I'm not sure.  You can set individual files to one or the other, or native, but I think you'd have to leave it without an svn:eol-style if you *wanted* to keep it mixed.  It'd be better to convert them first if there's no compelling reason for them to be mixed.\r\n\r\nhttp://svnbook.red-bean.com/en/1.1/ch07s02.html#svn-ch-7-sect-2.3.5 is the relevant section of the subversion book.\r\n\r\nThe algorithm would be:\r\n - find all files we want to have proper eol's\r\n - convert them all to your native system's eol's\r\n - for each filename in files:\r\n - - svn propset svn:eol-style native filename\r\n - commit all files\r\n\r\nThe above is obviously most easily done with a script.\r\n\r\nTo keep things nice going forward after this is done, if each committer added the following section to their .subversion/config then new files would automatically have the correct eol style set:\r\n[auto-props]\r\n*.java = svn:eol-style=native\r\n*.properties = svn:eol-style=native\r\n*.py= svn:eol-style=native\r\n*.sh = svn:eol-style=native;svn:executable\r\n*.thrift = svn:eol-style=native\r\n*.txt = svn:eol-style=native\r\n*.xml = svn:eol-style=native","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=euphoria","name":"euphoria","emailAddress":"michael dot greene at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Michael Greene","active":true},"created":"2009-07-03T02:58:53.705+0000","updated":"2009-07-03T02:58:53.705+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12423791/comment/12734731","id":"12734731","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=eweaver","name":"eweaver","emailAddress":"evan at cloudbur dot st","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Evan Weaver","active":true},"body":"I doubt the svn-magic will play well with Git.\r\n\r\nCan we switch to Unix endings and be done with it?","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=eweaver","name":"eweaver","emailAddress":"evan at cloudbur dot st","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Evan Weaver","active":true},"created":"2009-07-23T19:11:56.829+0000","updated":"2009-07-23T19:11:56.829+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12423791/comment/12734741","id":"12734741","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=euphoria","name":"euphoria","emailAddress":"michael dot greene at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Michael Greene","active":true},"body":"The svn-magic plays just fine with Git, git-svn knows about eol-style.  Even so, people not using git-svn and just using git directly would ignore the settings.\r\n\r\nRe: Unix endings, yeah, I was suggesting moving to Unix endings.  Settings those styles allows editors and platforms without appropriate eol handling to treat them natively though.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=euphoria","name":"euphoria","emailAddress":"michael dot greene at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Michael Greene","active":true},"created":"2009-07-23T19:24:04.045+0000","updated":"2009-07-23T19:24:04.045+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12423791/comment/12734825","id":"12734825","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jmhodges","name":"jmhodges","email